## Single-cell combinatorial indexing WGBS bioinformatics pipeline

## inputs
code_location=/project/RDS-FMH-DementiaCFDNA-RW/local_lib/code/scimet_scripts

## pipeline
1. convert bcl to fastq files using bcl2fastq2 software (installed on Artemis); 
${code_location}/bcl2fastq_scimet.sub

2. combine all lanes of run, rename and split I2 to I2 & I3
${code_location}/merge_fq.sh 

3. Demultiplexing R1, then demultiplex R2 by rename
${code_location}/CPT_HiSeq_fq_to_methCPT_split_hamming_PerLane_SE.pl

4. FastQC pre-trim


5. Trimming


6. FastQC post-trim


7. Alignment to human-mouse-pUC19-Lambda hybrid genome using scBS-MAP


8. Split alignment to single-cells


# Notes
• bbmap (installed on Artemis)
• scBS-MAP (Dependencies: SAMtools, bowtie2, BS-Seeker2 (This requires bowtie2, python2.6 or higher, pysam)). From this, install BS-Seeker and pysam.
• bamtools (installed on Artemis)
• CGmap tools (not installed on Artemis)
• Clustering (Can be done using SciKit-learn - not installed on Artemis)

